body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to Car Excellence! My name is Jacob Rivera and I will be assisting you today. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, Jacob. My name is Victoria Morris.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hi, Victoria. Thank you. To assist you better, could you kindly provide me with your phone number? Just spell out each digit, please.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course. It's seven one eight, five five five, nine eight zero zero.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. And for our records, could you also share your address but spelling out the house number and each word in the street name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure thing. Its one two three, Elm Street, apartment one zero zero two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Perfect, thank you for that. Your privacy is important to us, Victoria. We will keep your information secure. Is there anything else you'd like to share or inquire about?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, thank you, Jacob. I feel relieved now. I appreciate your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Victoria. Thank you for contacting us. If you have any further questions, feel free to reach out. Have a great day!
